- Recognition: CDP A for Scope 1 & 2; CDP B for Scope 3; Sustainalytics Medium Risk ~23.7 and ranked 4/98 in Aerospace & Defense (June 2025). [howmet (id 6-2)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGjkFqQHRGocSZq_98WFN1GtzUvmqQ8wRUYZZ_5JBkIm8bP5k76CMogYggJiPCabb4OJHwhFiXzAL9TO9D6E_AgKUiZVTVTHALsKqMNL4kt0Sy17eQKYtLA4k9oG_2QfhMNjFnavbY_LEROnENutTW2zQMY_2TKqyl_XTjQlJcmp3fDjnWj6Q6MUcs2Aft2w2XIupKqY8O16f0Jbd7Vrwe7RhrjgLX7Ag==) [sustainalytics (id 6-8)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFlhU2DuEm17PnzVMoMO0E3yRbjcO-in-PZfFR86nIOJ5iGzzTW8Kdo1VXq9aOv72eR933SKDFYak2Cc4eqNDhEr5q7CsGJhIDLT7kmaF29Dd2hg_eNUozDSAIRqqQVCiNJHQdgjr00q4AC2VFQQ5UyQMZu_Djw3hslJOTy4YCNdmdZfA==).

Why 17/25: The company has clear, validated environmental outcomes (21.7% absolute reduction in Scope 1 & 2 since 2019, intensity improvements and product CO2 claims), which put it into the “strong measurable impact” band. It doesn’t reach the top band (>50% improvement levels or company‑wide transformational resource savings) and Scope 3 reductions (the dominant portion of total emissions) are not yet committed quantitatively.

Future Strategy (11/15) — findings and evidence
- Near‑term and medium‑term targets: Howmet has set/achieved a 2024 target (21.5% ↓) and set a 2027 target (33.6% absolute ↓ in Scope 1 & 2 vs 2019). Company states a 2030 planning horizon for deeper reductions and net‑zero by 2050 ambition; some capital and project funding (e.g., initial US$9M approved for energy efficiency, additional investments in energy projects; historically $28.3M into >100 projects identified) are in place. [howmet (id 2-3)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEgBS7dDo2Ns44QI39ksCwWTkTSJmzgHXafUKvghi51wwor5IXTmiRzGTI1A5L75Nn3RCc7xL-XmeqwWcCEuZXXuDOzFXJMGroii-IoFsQ3ZpAAz9tKwuxuBVda8SxWZgbCa4pmDnNSjTnBxo7jRByTodLc4hJYUOSUAstqyiYsdyPCLlv0xRYP) [howmet (id 5-2)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEsjcjyj7vZiqLy_g9LTHL5OJuDGrhuawrqe9T5e5ZzuehBmkYE9MpzatI8hmHZ19Rbseyn0pQpfhbJA6CwAISMVA1gw1qmd4IaTghuzlbRlMlchxLf41nAPf58A8PhBtrLosOjOC2HLA1XNb0jf7Iu9K8MsCGsPnL00ZzyhUOMxlxviRKSG-7ohkaeAu-dQ_XNsF6pKgksMe00OpBKynvtx9iHwHSGTg==) [howmet (id 4-3)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEZPdzxPHZN9WE1gp3ga3YfmGLn7RA2N_W2XUxOrsMkdOkXpMYsAItZcn9DwY4NH3ZRdpFwuUTB_-BOmttz7u1sqy3PtMQOp2UjxorEhL3Chv70yGroy1bdjhOms59GW3CW-IKPVnmauPTtl6dyOtsB0jb9vFG5XFhd9BvSCsU3hYUHBqIXu6Zo) [howmet (id 3-5)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEnaMkvWxwPhjv9DAXALW5L3HqE9Z2nofb_x5eRPFRsROe5IV4tu5tMpApV5jTygf7ztYr53cNlL5zGxlAuw1NqA09VwV00TI2EQ3sUtb2ZmZ8JXBKJug-fQl_Y1kpFxON5QAqJxvoGrUeJnP3tQdKmq_7vZaXEx7n33bjVyMLRx1qRLulOoG9cxKtLnOCpYGFmmTsjqfBWF1AI_jzTQ0f-bGdcg7vQpJ0=).
- Roadmap features: double materiality assessment, strengthened ESG reporting (GRI/SASB/TCFD), supplier sustainability program with assessments, third‑party verification of some emissions categories, and an investment pipeline for energy projects—these show an organized roadmap. [howmet (id 4-0)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF-sMSGUwyPFZCUZp8KWlkybyk_YaX7LItH3yCRpkz3LCvBbLs3u-V3142DqRndrPganHCJP8y5rX4alUgyK5F5KTwZz2AveWkPzOiTNcOTgekykiLPMnG09Sny5rjAkMqH35YzS7RYR0Wyl7agBLEXvCs933NFJ4ig_y7imboEFk9Tn1ts1_reGVzSwcxUI7ZaOd6v2Rtif5IuwhHXXfhEA4tDZFnx8bw=) [howmet (id 3-13)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGMYxnTZS-0FGPhCrSBMapJvJWwld0jdUt2BgBqq2lJHZ2JAodSAk91FAvUqXZYbP050egvZ2YBbzEc4oIk7X6Xj6u9VnIcir-a1jEjlJbRzQd6vv_W31z6lvXFiViYFfoj9atjsXMR5D9lesx8Xhltm0BFct4XBcC_MaQQnZcdTiJYVh1Ms0ddM6hiRAmOegXh7dWC_FFyhHySbq4cv-kZx-eHm71i83rBqG4nD_QQfDG5s4fkR1e-zA==) [howmet (id 5-4)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGk03efLM8CxPNHwtcoJuRicxFf1dk4JxH46EjxDVKFgfvS6AkQAhK-OzTARicCN6tP3JPht197juqOT_RfCM0jw1_AW49-lNKZgGIw2HgTDbRP5WyOpVLw27kzWeGfE1FvnAb1KqgK76E=).
- Gaps: Scope 3 lacks a quantitative reduction target as of April 2025 (company cites data maturity constraints); supplier goal-setting underway but not yet fully public/quantified. [howmet (id 5-2)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEsjcjyj7vZiqLy_g9LTHL5OJuDGrhuawrqe9T5e5ZzuehBmkYE9MpzatI8hmHZ19Rbseyn0pQpfhbJA6CwAISMVA1gw1qmd4IaTghuzlbRlMlchxLf41nAPf58A8PhBtrLosOjOC2HLA1XNb0jf7Iu9K8MsCGsPnL00ZzyhUOMxlxviRKSG-7ohkaeAu-dQ_XNsF6pKgksMe00OpBKynvtx9iHwHSGTg==) [howmet (id 5-3)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHMD2ZpZ3IzyBUGh3h1-_3a7aiXgfEVUxAS2vvZBXMvd0IQu7pkGYwGgqR4Dja5cvq4ua8oxPqSmRdtKPxNUzFMZQJROMqoq41yXUDMHAbDZLTUXXNeDjI8kc9kHubzm9CgnoU7Ad8YjdK5vu6K3F5fJDv3TX8QPsJqfOqJvIerGEl5ltjdS68=).

Why 11/15: Howmet has a documented, funded near‑term roadmap and credible medium‑term targets for Scopes 1 & 2, strong reporting and verification practice, and active supplier engagement — but the absence of a mature, quantified Scope 3 reduction target (and more specific 2030 technology deployment commitments) prevents it reaching the top tier.

Industry Position (8/10) — findings and evidence
