Key risks & gaps (so you can weigh the score)
- Scope 3: The largest share of Howmet’s emissions is Scope 3 (purchased metals ≈66% of Scope 3). As of April 2025, no quantitative Scope 3 reduction target is published — the company is prioritizing supplier data quality and plans supplier‑focused goals. [howmet (id 5-1)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGvuhKf3UW60ecI3kMNU0WUku6ntjjfm6QVOdUYF5bH65OWqxHgOKfDpXBamtAnO38fvu9A6gIAH1pAjSa0BniseXeHcjUNr6h-dwjZrEtvnlP4qn-_UkKPiLAOiSzNgbYcfxPoWrjcg2LCRT1JAJ5sb2eUsYcsB3qTLoKq5E-orLtoiQn8HliWaEX-JszKw0fs2_ZHOdYaV0FAekV4S5j1Nfh9U0TZDQ==) [howmet (id 5-2)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEsjcjyj7vZiqLy_g9LTHL5OJuDGrhuawrqe9T5e5ZzuehBmkYE9MpzatI8hmHZ19Rbseyn0pQpfhbJA6CwAISMVA1gw1qmd4IaTghuzlbRlMlchxLf41nAPf58A8PhBtrLosOjOC2HLA1XNb0jf7Iu9K8MsCGsPnL00ZzyhUOMxlxviRKSG-7ohkaeAu-dQ_XNsF6pKgksMe00OpBKynvtx9iHwHSGTg==).
- Operational incidents: Historical local emissions compliance fines were reported at some sites (Cleveland, Bestwig), indicating compliance and localized environmental management risk areas that need management attention. [energymonitor (id 3-1)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH7OVKsioViwiFXLuMHhnH6gZJHZKQKGEIUiNPNStMK2UFRSQBWjg2d0TE5S-xq2PaH64GtpbBiFcAm4IC1hKPLgT2PSiQV0hIOOTBC5Ja_kpWMdA76VowlzDqRZKflBt6IDO9DabbHVW-jsS-Q28DcHvpJG9r95F9krlhrITyE2LcgUEGl).
- Scale of breakthrough tech: Much of Howmet’s sustainability advantage flows from process/product improvement and efficient materials engineering (highly valuable) rather than owning/monetizing a disruptive low‑carbon platform at scale beyond their markets.

